<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chap-logic">
  <title>Logic and the Language of Proofs</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      In order to read and construct proofs,
      we need to start with the language in which they are written:
      <em>logic.</em> Logic is to mathematics what grammar is to English.
      <xref ref="sec_prop">Section</xref>
      will not look particularly mathematical,
      but we'll quickly get to work in <xref ref="sec_proof">Section</xref>
      using logic in a mathematical context.
    </p>
  </introduction>
